4:
Call me to mind, Yahweh, when you show favor to your people;
\q help me when you save them.
\q

6:
We have sinned like our ancestors;
\q we have done wrong, and we have done evil.
\q

7:
Our fathers did not appreciate your marvelous deeds in Egypt;
\q they ignored your many acts of covenant faithfulness;
\q they were rebellious at the sea, the Sea of Reeds.

11:
But the waters covered their adversaries;
\q not one of them survived.
\q

13:
But they quickly forgot what he had done;
\q they did not wait for his instructions.
\q

24:
Then they despised the fruitful land;
\q they did not believe his promise,
\q
